HEADWORD: Trigamous
<hw>Trig"a*mous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>trigamus</ets> a thrice-married man, Gr. <?/ thrice married; <?/
(see <er>Tri-</er>) + <?/ marriage: cf. F. <ets>trigame</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having three sorts of flowers in the same head,
-- male, female, and hermaphrodite, or perfect, flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
